review_blob: My numerical ratings are based on the draft version of Newky Brown, as the bottled product often tastes a bit like fuel oil. On draft its an entirely different experience, with a refreshing taste which has the unfortunate characteristic of encouraging the consumption of just one more, even after Ive had one more.

NB 1554 is one of the blessings of modern life. I originally bought 1 bottle, not knowing what to expect from its dark appearance. It has none of the overpowering nature present in some dark beers, but instead possesses a gentle, drinkable nature. Its kind of like an ultra-dark amber lager, and I now buy it by the case (when I can find it).
Its better than ordinary Budweiser, and has more alcohol, but still lacks flavor. The presence of visible Belgian lace is a departure from the usual A-B product. Its potable.
